Digital forensic analysis is rapidly becoming an integral part of incident response capitalising on a steady increase in the number of trained forensic investigators and forensic toolkits available Strangly despite the increased interest in and focus on forensics within the information security industry there is surprisingly little discussion of anti forensics In an attempt to remedy the lack of the most common Linux file system ext2fs To facilitate a useful discussion of anti forensic strategies it is important that the reader possess certain background information In particular the of coverage available to these topics and the interested reader is directed to the references which discuss them in greater depth
